---
description: React component and hook architecture rules
globs:
  - "**/*.tsx"
  - "**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: true
---

# react.mdc

- Use functional components only
- Prefer declarative patterns
- Keep components small and focused
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Avoid deeply nested JSX
- Prefer composition over prop drilling
- Avoid unnecessary useEffect usage
- Use useEffect only for synchronization with external systems
- Prefer derived state over duplicated state
- Use memoization only when measurable benefits exist
- Prefer controlled components for complex forms
- Keep UI components presentation-focused
- Avoid over-engineering abstractions
- Prefer readable code over clever code
- Use React 19 patterns and APIs when appropriate